postcontent:
FA91 battle rifle in .308. This is an HK91 clone built by Federal Arms Corp.

THE SCOPE IS NOT FOR SALE.

For more info, here is a great review about the rifle - http://www.ar15armory.com/forums/Federal-Arms-FA91-t2421.html

It is functionally perfect - POA = POI, I have never had a single problem with it, and it has gladly eaten anything I have fed it. Internals are in great shape, bore is flawless. I am not 100% sure I accurately remember the exact headspace measurement from the last I checked it, but I believe it was .010, which is well within spec.

Cosmetically it is in overall very good shape, with some scratches on the compensator and cocking tube, and touched-up but formerly chipped paint around the ejection port. The linked photos are an accurate representation of the condition.

It currently wears a CETME styled wooden handguard and black synthetic stock and pistol grip furniture. The pistol grip I believe was originally green and painted over. The buttstock is a solid slab - it does not have the usual sling attachment point or pin holes.

Federal Arms was bought out by Century a few years back, but this was NOT built by the Century monkeys, it pre-dates Century. Nothing on this gun has been ground. It is built on a DC Industries receiver, which is the same milled receiver used by Springfield Armory for their SAR-8 clone of the HK 91. It is a flat-top with the full-length picatinny rail.

Accessories :

    10 pre-ban 20 round magazines (7 shown in picture)
    Black handguard
    Green pistol grip, handguard & buttstock with standard sling mount and pin holes
    CETME style wood buttstock. One hole for attaching the buttstock is split because it was not properly pre-drilled and a screw went in crooked, but it is an easy fix (re-drill) and will hold securely. I just haven't bothered because personally I dosn't care for the wood look on this gun.
     217 rounds of ATI Turkish 7.62x51 (which currently go for $12.99 box of 20). I do not have a spare travel ammo case so you would need to bring your own for transport.
     CTD plastic gun case    
3-ring binder full of printed manuals including HK G3 Armorer's Manual, HK G3 Manual, various schematics and parts lists, etc.

Selling Terms : FTF on FA-10, or FFL at buyer's expense if desired.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Arsenal SA RPK-7 Limited Edition 46 of 300 MILLED
postcontent:
This weapon is listed on Gunbroker with over 40 pics.  Check it out, the auction number is 263649337

This is a LIKE NEW Arsenal SA RPK-7. These weapons are US made, chambered in 7.62 x 39mm, and feature a MILLED receiver, RPK heavy barrel (23.2"), 14mm muzzle threads, muzzle nut, folding bipod, cleaning rod inside bipod, no bayonet lug, beautiful blonde wood furniture, paddle style buttstock with hole for cleaning kit. These milled receivers are the best AK receivers on the planet. They are smoother, more accurate, and more reliable than their stamped cousins. 

The woman I purchased it from claimed it belonged to her husband, who passed away several years ago. He took it to the range once to "test it out" and put it in the safe. You can see in the pictures the side of the receiver is not scratched yet from moving the safety lever. There is a 75 round drum, a 30 round steel magazine, a 40 round steel magazine, and one that she claimed holds 61 rounds. I only had 41 rounds of ammo laying around, and that filled the middle mag. You can see in the pictures the extra length of that other monster magazine. I cannot confirm its capacity. 

I took as many photos as I could. One shows the ONLY blemish on this weapon and that is a small mark on the stock. One photo of the bipod leg shows the cleaning rod inside it, and a couple of other odd pics are showing the bipod feet and hinge are not scratched. The dust cover and button are not scratched from removal. This weapon is nearly flawless! 

From what I can gather, this weapon is a Limited Edition #46 of 300 Arsenal produced in 2003 and did not plan on doing another run of these and are not in stock on Arsenal's site. 

http://www.arsenalinc.com/usa/product.php?productid=59&cat=51&page=1 


Let the photos tell their own story. Good luck, thanks for looking, and happy bidding! 

This rifle must go to the FFL of your choice. Make sure you know the laws in your state and if it is legal for you to own this rifle and/or magazines. I WILL NOT ship to California!
